.TH ENCHANT-@ENCHANT_MAJOR_VERSION@ 1
.SH NAME
Enchant \- list provider and dictionary information, and do basic batch spell-checking
.SH SYNOPSIS
.ll +8
.B enchant-@ENCHANT_MAJOR_VERSION@
[\fIOPTION\fR...] [\fIFILE...\fR]
.ll -8
.br
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Enchant
gives information about Enchant\(cqs spell-checker providers and the dictionaries each offers.
See \fBenchant\fR(5) for details about how the providers and dictionaries are located.
It can also list misspelled words in input files or standard input.
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-dictionary\fR \fIDICTIONARY\fR
use the given dictionary
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-check-spelling\fR
List misspellings in the input files, or standard input if none given.
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-pwl\fR \fIWORDLIST\fR
use the given personal wordlist
.TP
\fB\-L\fR, \fB\-\-show\-lines\fR
display line numbers
.TP
.B "\-\-list-providers"
List spelling providers.
.TP
.B "\-\-list\-dictionaries"
List all dictionaries, and which provider will be used for each.
.TP
.B "\-\-default\-dictionary"
Show the default dictionary for the given or default language.
.TP
.B "\-\-word\-chars"
Show the extra word characters for the given or default language, if available. This is of little interest to most users.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
display help and exit
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
display version information and exit
.SH FILES AND DIRECTORIES
See
.BR enchant (5)
for details of configuration files and personal word lists.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR enchant (5),
.BR aspell (1),
